			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I read these forms every so often, and i always see quotes like..<br> <br>&quot;any necro worth a grain of salt can beat a mage in a duel&quot;<br><br>And if a mage states that he did infact beat a necro he is instantly shot down ans told that the necro probably just sucked.<br><br>I will tell everyone right now that Mage &gt; Necro, and i will also clear up a few rumers.<br><br>First off, i hear alot the reason a necro would always win is because they have deflux.. lol that is the dumbest excuse ever. Want to know a secret, deflux may be a fast cast, but its range is about as far as i can piss. The range on deflux is between 50 and 100, the range on scares of sigle is 450-500. <br><br>All you gota do is run in external camera so you can see you and him, stop to cast scares, if he starts casting run.. he will never pull off a deflux on you.<br><br>Second, i hear these little crying voices &quot;ohh what if he fears me&quot; well i'll tell you what, if your MR is low enough to get feared in PVP you deserve to die, just &quot;shielding&quot; adds like 20 MR, anything over 70 and you wont get feared, when i duel casters i average 170 MR, NEVER gotten feared in 50+ necro duels.<br><br>Finaly is the real threat, if they fear your pet. Most smart necros know that if the battle lasts longet than 30 seconds the mage pet is going to be digesting the necro pet and on its way for some caster luv'in. So SOME necros(most think they can just deflux you to death), but some will try and fear your pet and sick theirs on you... this is a HUGE gamble, fear sticking to the pet is about 50/50. 1. it cost them mana, 2. gives you time to get in a couple free pot shots. to give a better example i have list 5-10 duels, out of 50+ from my pet getting feared, and that will end very soon as i almost have fearless companion.<br><br>Just a few hints for you necro killers out there.<br><br>1. the malosi line of spells overwrites all forms of shielding, MALO is great at this because its totaly unresistable, so you land one of those any the necro loses about 300 max hp's pluse 20-30 MR.<br><br>2. Despite how you all hear about necros being Dis/Poi based, those are their dots, and those dots are 10-20 second casting time so no way in hell would they ever use them in a duel, look more for FIRE and MAGIC resistance(includeing your fire shield)<br><br>3. have a dispell staff on you and your top buff slot open. I cast see invis first then buff, then click off see invis. this way i can easly fry any dot/movement speed spell he tries to land.<br><br><br>Hope this helps <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile" border="0" /> --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT="<img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile" border="0" />"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   and no matter what, enjoy the fight. <p></p><i></i></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
