			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">In the Arena zone or on a PvP server, a mage stands a decent chance.<br><br>In the Bazarre arena or in a duel, the mage is at a terrible disadvantage.<br><br>Basically you need room to run and the ability to dispell your pet.  If you can do those two things, you can give a necro a hard time.<br><br>This is also assuming your resists are normal PvP resists -- with a full suit of diamond/BD gear and basic non-TOV non-Kael 50+ gear, your resists should be 90-150 in all areas unbuffed.  A full suit (9 pieces) of diamond/BD gear costs 15k on my server.  That's enough to resist necro DOTs, poisons, diseases and screaming terror 99% of the time.<br><br>I'm pretty sure Pyrocuror isn't lure based either, if that's what that person meant.  It doesn't take 250 FR to resist it 50 percent of the time.  I know when I played a 60 necro for a week (borrowed a friend's), Pyrocuror was far from guarenteed to land on PvP vets with 150+ FR.  (I hope I'm remember the spell name right -- the highest upgrade to Boil Blood is the one I'm thinking of.  Certainly easier to land than darkness, but it's no Lure.)<br><br>Basically the key is to keep your pet in the fight.  If it's an epic pet, this won't take long.  If it's non-epic, you'll have to work harder.  If your pet gets impaired by any necro spells and you can't dispell it quickly, run.<br><br>Really, the biggest problem is that dispelling the necro can cause your pet to poof unless you're really careful and can type &quot;/pet back off&quot; at the right time.<br> <p></p><i></i></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
